The paper deals with generating 3D shapes and their associated semantics and structure, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of graph neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the ability to discover shape structure from un-annotated images, which could involve natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
